vfsCore

Class CoreIO

  • java.lang.Object
    • vfsCore.CoreIO

  • public class CoreIO
extends java.lang.Object
    The CoreIO manages all the input/output methods. It is an interface between the Core manipulating the hierarchy, and the .dsk file where the VFS disk is stored The .dsk has a specific structure, described in our report. It is composed of (and in this order) : - the data of the files stored on the VFS, - a serialized version of the hierarchy, - the desired size of the disk (ie the size of the part of the file dedicated to storing the data).
    Author:
    Simon Rodriguez
